episodes.episodeDesc: King Robert has taken his family and entourage to visit his old friend Ned at Winterfell in The North. Ned's already sizeable household adopts six abandoned direwolves.//p//Meanwhile in the Free City of Pentos Viserys is arranging the marriage of his sister Daenerys to Dothraki Khal Drogo.//p//First Appearance: Ned, Catelyn, Robb, Sansa, Arya, Bran, Rickon, Jon, Theon, Benjen, Robert, Cersei, Jaime, Tyrion, Joffrey, Myrcella, Tommen, Sandor, Hodor, Rodrik, Jory, Luwin, Ros, Ghost, Grey Wind, Summer, Shaggydog, Daenerys, Viserys, Drogo, Jorah, Qotho

Ned and his daughters are on the way to King's Landing with the royal party but there is canine trouble as Joffrey and the butcher's boy are attacked by a wolf and hound respectively.//p//Jon, Tyrion and Benjen are heading North stopping only to pick up a fresh delivery of rapists for the Night's Watch.//p//Khal Drogo and his new khaleesi arrive in the Dothraki Sea where Daenerys gets a couple of new handmaidens.//p//First Appearance:Rast, Doreah, Irri.

Ned and the King arrive in The Crownlands where they meet with the Small Council. Whilst his wife Catelyn and Ser Rodrik try and sneak into King's Landing unnoticed.//p//Beyond the wall Jon Snow arrive at Castle Black and meets and beats his new Night's Watch comrades. //p//Viserys threatens Daenerys which leads to a whipping from Rakharo.//p//First Appearance: Joer Mormont, Maester Aemon, Yoren, Alliser Thorne, Grenn, Pyp, Lord Baelish, Lord Varys, Renly, Pycelle, Ser Barristan, Rakharo.

At the wall Sam arrives at Castle Black and wishes he hasn't, whilst further south the Three-Eyed Raven appears to Bran in his avian form.//p//In the Riverlands Catelyn and Ser Rodrik stop at an inn and bump into Tyrion who has just made a useful introduction to sellsword Bronn.//p//At King's Landing Ned has turned detective to track down Gendry but his key witness is silenced by a lance to the throat from the Mountain.//p//First Appearance: Sam, Three-eyed Raven, Bronn, Gendry, Gregor Clegane, Janos Slynt.

Catelyn and party are attacked by the hill tribes as they take Tyrion to the Vale to meet Lysa Arryn and her lactose tolerant son Robin.//p//Ser Loras engages in some horse play to defeat the Mountain who then resorts to some extreme animal cruelty.//p//Jaime attacks Ned outside Littlefinger's brothel and Jory gets to see the Kingslayer's dagger up close.//p//First Appearance: Lysa Arryn, Robin Arryn, Ser Loras//p//Death: Jory Cassel

Ned is reinstated as Hand of the King and in the abscence of Robert, who is combining his twin passions of hunting and drinking, sends Beric Dondarrion in pursuit of the Mountain who is misbehaving in the Riverlands.//p//Bran is attacked by wildlings whilst riding. Robb and Theon kill most of them but spare Osha.//p//In the Vale Tyrion demands a trial by combat and Bronn obliges thoughtfully disposing of his defeated enemies body through the built in rubbish chute.//p// Across the narrow sea Daenerys has just enjoyed a delicious raw horse's heart when her brother starts making a scene. He demands a crown of gold and Drogo immediately complies proving it pays to be assertive.//p//First Appearance: Osha, Beric Dondarrion//p//Death: Viserys Targaryen

Sam and Jon take the oath of the Night's Watch but Jon doesn't get the job he'd hoped for.//p//Jaime visits his father Tywin who is preparing for war with Robb Stark by skinning a stag.//p//Jorah foils a wineseller's plot to poison Daenerys.//p//King Robert succumbs to hunting injuries after declaring Ned Protector of the Realm. Cersei rips up the decree and Ned is betrayed by Littlefinger and the City Watch who kill his men.//p//First Appearance: Tywin Lannister//p//Death: King Robert
